html.body: Cholesterol is the origin of multitude of steroids, which are of high importance in metabolic processes. The common synthesis path starts with the partial removal of the cholesterol side chain, yielding the gestagen progesterone. Removal of the remaining side chain leads to androgens, a further aromatozation of ring A yields estrogens.free text=Biochemical Pathways - An atlas of Biochemistry and Molecular Biology - Gerhard Michal
